The Maxwell House Hotel served our original roast coffee to its guests in 1892; it was so popular, the hotel quickly ran out and returned to its regular coffee. After patrons complained, the hotel served our original roast exclusively.

Maxwell House Coffee

A good day starts with a good cup of coffee. That’s why we custom roast every batch for the perfect balance of strength and flavor. Say good morning with the coffee that’s Good to the Last Drop, one cup at a time.

Whether you're in the mood for dark coffee, light coffee, medium roast coffee or even decaf coffee, you can enjoy a good cup with Maxwell House.

Read more

Good to the Last Drop, No Matter How You Brew It

Ground Coffee

When you need more than a single cup, brew up a pot of our rich, remarkable coffee. Available in 14 varieties.

Coffee Singles

No coffeemaker needed; use these coffee bags like tea and add hot water. Each individually wrapped filter bag of our Original Roast Coffee delivers the delicious taste and aroma that you expect from Maxwell House. Available in regular and decaf.

Instant Coffee

Our Instant Coffee is a true American Classic. Remarkably rich with perfectly balanced flavor. Our easy to store jar closes tightly to help keep coffee fresh. Available in regular and decaf.

K-Cup Pods

Now you can enjoy the delicious taste and aroma that you expect from Maxwell House one cup at a time with our convenient K-Cup Pods, made for your Keurig coffee machine (compatible with 1.0/2.0 models). Available in 9 roasts.

Read more

Product description

Maxwell House Medium Roast House Blend Ground Coffee has a consistent signature taste that is good to the last drop. This medium body coffee is exceptionally smooth with a balanced flavor and is the perfect start to your day. Made with 100% pure coffee beans, this house blend roast coffee is great served black or with cream and sugar. Brew a pot of this smooth Kosher coffee in any drip coffee maker. Maxwell House coffee is packaged in a 24.5 ounce resealable canister of ground coffee to lock in flavor between uses. From lively light roasts to full bodied dark blends, Maxwell Houses signature taste is created through a process that isnt done the easy way, but the right way, for 125 years.

How does Amazon calculate star ratings?
Amazon calculates a product’s star ratings based on a machine learned model instead of a raw data average. The model takes into account factors including the age of a rating, whether the ratings are from verified purchasers, and factors that establish reviewer trustworthiness.
